<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spain Defeates Slovenia 2-1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSLES, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Spain struggled to beat Slovenia
2-1 on Sunday and left the tiny nation on the brink of elimination
in the Euro 2000 Group C match in Amsterdam, the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Joseba Etxeberria scored the crucial goal for a
disappointing Spanish team, beating Slovenian goalkeeper Mladen
Dabanovic at his near post on the hour, just a minute after
Slovenia had tied.
</P>
<P>
Spain is now equal on three points with Norway who meets
Yugoslavia later on Sunday. Slovenia and Yugoslavia have a point
each.
</P>
<P>
Slovenian Zlatko Zahovic claimed the 2-2 equaliser in the 66th
minute - his third goal of the tournament - after both he and
teammate Milan Osterc went for a cross.
</P>
<P>
They appeared to impede each other but the ball bobbled past
wrong-footed Spanish goalkeeper Santiago Canizares and television
replays showed Zahovic had got the vital touch.
</P>
<P>
The goal woke up the Spaniards, who had been cruising after
Raul shot them into a fourth minute lead. The Spanish striker
cracked home a half volley from 16 meters when a loose ball
dropped to him.
</P>
<P>
Spanish coach Jose Antonio Camacho made four changes to his
starting line-up following that defeat, introducing goalkeeper
Canizares, defender Abelardo, midfielder Gaizka Mendieta, and
Alfonso to partner Raul up front.
</P>
<P>
Slovenia was unchanged from the side which had led Yugoslavia
3-0 in its opener before being pegged back to 3-3 in a remarkable
match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
