<HEADLINE> UEFA Threatens to Kick Englandd our of Euro 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- UEFA's executive committee has
theatened to exclude England from the European championship if its
fans continue to cause violence, according to reports from Liege,
Belgium reaching here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"UEFA will have to consider the future presence of the English
team if there is any more violence," Gerard Aigner, chief
executive of UEFA, was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
UEFA president Lennart Johansson, asked if England could be
kicked out of Euro 2000, replied: "That cannot be excluded."
</P>
</TEXT>
