<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Slovenia Unlucky to Lose, Says Katanec </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Slovenia's coach Srecko Katanec
said he thought his team was unlucky to lose 2-1 to Spain at Euro
2000 on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"Spain were no better than we were tonight -- my boys did the
best they could," Katanec quoted by Slovenian television as saying.
</P>
<P>
"Once more we all have to take our hats off to our boys," he
said referring to their brilliant performance in the 3-3 draw with
Yugoslavia on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"We played a very good match again. We proved we can be very
dangerous opponents to anyone if we start with an offensive
playing style. Every team will always have problems against our
attacking play."
</P>
<P>
Asked about Slovenia's next match with Norway which his team
must win to have a chance of reaching the quarter-finals,Katanec
said: "We will try to beat Norway, that is our duty."
</P>
<P>
Spanish coach Jose Antonio Camacho, asked whether Spain should
have done better, made a blunt response: "Those people don't know
very much about football."
</P>
<P>
"The game was very hard. You must bear in mind that it was
very hot. But our aim was to win and we did that."  
</P>
</TEXT>
