<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2110GMT, Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS -- Bashar al-Assad, the son of the late Syrian
president Hafez al-Assad, on Sunday was appointed leader of Syria's
ruling Baath party which is holding its ninth congress.
</P>
<P>
Bashar is expected to be elected secretary-general of the party
at the end of the congress, which is due to end Wednesday, the
official SANA news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Observers said it is almost certain that the 1,021 delegates
attending the congress are to give approval to Bashar's
appointment. (BC-Syria-Bashar-Party Leader)
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israel's coalition crisis with Shas party is
nearing solution as Shas representatives and One Israel negotiators
have reached agreements on almost all of the disputed issues,
Israel Radio reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Prime Minister Ehud Barak has provided more time for
the two sides to reach an agreement on resolving the coalition
crisis by postponing Sunday's cabinet meeting to Tuesday, at which
Shas was announced to submit the resignation of its ministers and
deputy ministers.
</P>
<P>
The two sides held another round of marathon meeting Saturday
night in Tel Aviv, which dealt with "how to implement the reform
plan for the Shas education network.(BC-Israel-Coalition Crisis)
</P>
<P>
ALGIERS -- Ethiopia and Eritrea signed here on Sunday morning a
cease fire deal to end their 2-year-long border dispute, according
to Algerian News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopian Foreign Minister Seyoum Mesfin and his Eritrean
counterpart Haile Woldensae inked the accord in an official
ceremony attended by Algerian president and current Organization of
African Unity (OAU) Chairman AbdelAziz Bouteflika, OAU Secretary
General Salim Ahmed Salim, U.S. Presidential envoy Anthony Lake, EU
envoy to the Horn of African Region Rino Seri and foreign
ambassadors in Algiers, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the ceremony, Bouteflika praised the deal as "a
historical event" which crowned the efforts made to restore peace
and stability in the Horn of Africa Region. (BC-Ethiopia-Eritrea-
Peace Accord)
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- United Nations Secretary General Kofi Annan arrived in
Cairo Sunday on the second leg of a Middle East trip mainly aimed
at ensuring Lebanon shall remain calm following Israel's withdrawal
from the country.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters upon arrival, Annan said there are some
problems over verification of Israeli withdrawal from Lebanon and
definition of the border, but both sides have agreed to solve the
issues in cooperation with the U.N.
</P>
<P>
Israel completed troop withdrawal from a border strip in
southern Lebanon on May 24, ending 22 years of occupation there.
(BC-Egypt-Annan-Visit) 
</P>
