<HEADLINE> Thorough Probe into Gas Explosion Promised </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 19 (Xinhua) -- A special committee would be
formed to investigate a gas explosion, which killed two Kuwaiti
engineers and lightly wounded four workers Sunday, said a Kuwaiti
official.
</P>
<P>
Oil Minister Sheikh Saud Nasser Al-Sabah told a parliamentary
session on Monday that "There will be a thorough investigation into
the accident," which happened to Unit Eight of the Shoeba Refinery.
</P>
<P>
The oil plant was established in l968 as one of the biggest
Hydrogen-operated oil purification plants in the world.
</P>
<P>
He promised to brief the parliament and the National Oil
Corporation (NOC) Staff Union on the investigation proceedings and
submit a detailed report upon conclusion of the probe.
</P>
<P>
NOC Chairman Hani Hussein said the accident occurred when one of
the engineers was trapped to death in an underway aircraft-fuel-
producing deposit and another died as he tried to rescue him.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Health, Social and Labor Affairs Committee under
the parliament was authorized to launch an inquiry into the general
situation in the oil refineries nationwide and submit a report in
three months to the parliament on its findings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
