<HEADLINE> Annan Names French Diplomat as Head of U.N. Peacekeeping Department </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 19 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan on Monday appointed Jean-Marie Guehenno of France as head of
the U.N. Department of peacekeeping Operations.
</P>
<P>
Jean-Marie Guehenno, who currently chairs the board of France'
s institute of Advanced Studies on National Defense, will replace
Bernard Miyet on October 1, 2000.
</P>
<P>
Miyet, also a French, assumed his post in January 1997. He
made clear that he would leave the post after two years of service.
</P>
<P>
Guehenno, 50, serves on a U.N. advisor council on disarmament
questions and is an advisor to the France's Cour des Comptes,
France's watchdog agency on public spending.
</P>
<P>
Guehenno was French ambassador to the Western European Union,
the European Union's Defense arm. He held various posts in the
French foreign ministry. He was a advisor to the President of the
European Union Bank and served as cultural adviser at the French
Embassy in New York in the early 1990s. 
</P>
