<HEADLINE> Argentine Trade Surplus with Mercosur Countries to Grow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 19 (Xinhua) -- During the first four months
of the year, Argentina's trade surplus with other Southern Common
Market Countries (Mercosur) increased by 127 percent compared with
last year's same period, arriving at 440 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to Ministry of Economy data, between January and
April of this year, exports to Mercosur countries reached 2.522
billion dollars, while imports summed up 2.082 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur, the largest economic bloc in South America, is
composed by Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay, with Bolivia
and Chile as associate members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
