<HEADLINE> Yemen Welcomes Ethiopia-Eritrea Peace Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Yemen said on Monday it is optimistic
about the implementation of a truce accord that Ethiopia and
Eritrea signed on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In a news briefing here on Monday, a foreign source stressed the
accord will create a favorable environment for a final
comprehensive solution for the border dispute between the two Horn
of African neighbors.
</P>
<P>
The source said Yemen spared no efforts toward approximating the
viewpoints of the two countries, adding Yemen is keen on the
stability of the Horn of Africa region and holds that dialogue is
always the ideal way to deal with such problems between neighboring
countries.
</P>
<P>
The accord will help tap the potential of both countries and
allow them time to handle the more pressing issues of development
and construction, the source stressed.
</P>
<P>
Yemen also regards the peace deal between Ethiopia and Eritrea
as a success by the Organization of African Unity (OAU) in settling
African conflicts peacefully, he hailed.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia and Eritrea signed in Algiers on Sunday morning a peace
deal to put an end to their two-year-long border dispute which left
huge human and property losses.  
</P>
</TEXT>
