<HEADLINE> Arab League Welcomes Eritrean-Ethiopian Peace Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League on Monday expressed
welcome to a peace agreement that Eritrea and Ethiopia signed on
Sunday to halt two years of armed conflicts over border disputes.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the league voiced the hope that the agreement
will be fully implemented in a bid to safeguard peace and stability
needed for social and economic development of the two countries of
the Horn of Africa.
</P>
<P>
In the peace agreement inked in Algiers, Algeria following
intensive mediation by the Organization of African Unity (OAU),
Addis Ababa and Asmara pledge to halt the border war that has
killed tens of thousands of people, displaced more than a million
others and caused heavy losses of properties on both sides.
</P>
<P>
The pan-Arab forum called on the international community to
provide humanitarian assistance to the refugees and the displaced
persons caused by the war.
</P>
<P>
It expressed appreciation for the role played by the OAU and its
current chairman Algerian President Abdelaziz Bouteflika in
brokering the truce.
</P>
<P>
Eritrea and Ethiopia have been at war with each other since May
l998 for several pieces of border land. Fighting erupted anew last
May along their 1,000-kilometer border. 
</P>
</TEXT>
