<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Canada's telecommunications giant
Nortel Networks Corp. offered 2,000 jobs and 3.3 million U.S.
dollars in scholarship in Europe Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Nortel Networks' leadership in Europe has never been stronger,
"where Nortel plans to increase its workforce by 10 percent this
year and invest in "Europe's youth, the future generation of
Internet leaders," said the company in a news release.
</P>
<P>
Nortel is employing 20,000 people in 33 European countries and
the new jobs and scholarships "will be predominantly available in
the UK, Ireland France, Germany, Italy and Spain," said the news
release.
</P>
<P>
Under its expansion plan, Notel will add two new Wireless
Centers of Excellence -- respectively in Spain and Germany -- to
complete its European network already based in the UK, France and
Italy.
</P>
<P>
The company will also open two new high performance internet
laboratories in Norway and Sweden. 
</P>
