<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng Arrives in Slovakia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRATISLAVA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC),
arrived here Monday on an official goodwill visit to Slovakia
after visiting Croatia.
</P>
<P>
Li is the highest-ranking official to have visited Slovakia
since China and Slovakia forged diplomatic relations in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival, Li and his wife were greeted at the airport
by Slovak National Council Vice-Chairman Igor Presperin.
</P>
<P>
At a welcoming ceremony at the airport, Li Peng, accompanied by
Presperin, reviewed an honor guard.
</P>
<P>
In his written speech issued at the airport, Li said that there
exist traditional friendship between the Chinese and Slovak
peoples. In recent years, he said, friendly cooperation between
the two countries in various fields has grown to the satisfaction
of both sides.
</P>
<P>
He said the purpose of his current visit is to increase
understanding, strengthen trust, promote friendship and deepen
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Slovakia, he said, he will meet with Slovak
leaders to discuss the possibility of further expanding
cooperation to the benefit of both sides, and exchange views on
other issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng is on a six-nation tour which has already taken him to
Yugoslavia, Slovenia and Croatia, and will also carry him to
Azerbaijan and Ukraine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
