when bodies of 54 men and four women were found from a
refrigerated truck at Dover, a major landing point for ferries
from France and Belgium.
</P>
<P>
The truck was a Dutch-registered vehicle and the driver was
already detained by police.
</P>
<P>
The truck reportedly left the Belgian port of Zeebrugge on
Sunday, the hottest day of the year so far in northwestern Europe
with the temperature hovering at 33 degrees Celsius. Suffocation
has been suspected to be the cause of death.
</P>
<P>
