<BODY>
<HEADLINE> European Education Conference Opens in Bucharest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 19 (Xinhua) -- European education ministers on
Monday started discussions about the goal of Europe's education
and how to achieve it at a conference held here.
</P>
<P>
Ministers and representatives from 35 European countries and
relevant institutions are expected to discuss "Social Cohesion and
Quality -- A Challenge for Education," the major topic at the two-
day meeting, local media reported.
</P>
<P>
Specifically, the discussions will involve topics such as
fairness in education, democracy in schools, the role of new
technologies in improving quality, management and efficiency in
the use of resources in the field of education.
</P>
<P>
The conference, the fourth of its kind, is co-sponsored by the
education ministries of Romania and Portugal with the support of
the EU's executive body, the European Commission.
</P>
<P>
The Conference of European Ministers of Education was launched
as a forum to talk about the most important education issues in
the region with an aim to enhance cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
