<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, June 19 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FEIRA, Portugal -- Greece became the 12th member of the
European Union's single currency mechanism after the EU summit on
Monday gave the final approval for its entry.
</P>
<P>
On January 1 next year, the euro is set to replace the Greek
currency of drachma to end the run of a 2,500-year-old currency. (
EU-Euro-Summit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The United States on Monday formally eased
economic sanctions against the Democratic People's Republic of
Korea (DPRK).
</P>
<P>
The move, published in the official Federal Register, allows
the DPRK to export raw materials and goods to the United States
and opens air and shipping routes between the two countries. (US-
DPRK-Sanctions)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The European Union (EU) is getting ready to
recognize a Palestinian state if one is declared in September,
whether by agreement with Israel or unilaterally, local daily
Ha'aretz reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
A special committee of EU officials is currently discussing the
status of the European consulates in Jerusalem after the EU
recognizes a Palestinian state with Jerusalem as its capital, the
paper added. (Palestinian-State)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
