PYONGYANG -- The Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK)
on Monday urged Japan to take concrete moves to push forward the
talks between the two countries, the Korean Central News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
After the historic summit between the leaders of DPRK and South
Korea, Japanese Prime Minister Yoshiro Mori has more than once
said "Japan has strong will and eagerness to improve the relations
with DPRK," said a commentary published by the news agency. (DPRK-
Japan-Call)
</P>
<P>
