<P>
LONDON -- The bodies of 58 people were found in the back of a
lorry at the English port of Dover early on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the Dutch-registered lorry, which arrived from
Zeebrugge, Belgium, just before midnight, has been arrested.
</P>
<P>
The 54 men and four women presumably of oriental origins were
thought to have been illegal immigrants. Two survivors, both men,
have been taken to hospital. (Britain-Lorry-Deaths)
</P>
