BEIRUT -- Lebanese Prime Minister Salim Hoss said in Beirut on
Monday that Lebanon wants U.N. peacekeeping force to end Israel's
continuous occupation on some parts of the Lebanese-Israeli border.
</P>
<P>
Speaking prior to a meeting with U.N. Secretary General Kofi
Annan, Hoss also said Lebanon holds the continuation of the
Israeli violation of the international border represents a
violation threatening the safety and sovereignty of Lebanese
territories that must not be allowed by the Security Council. (
Lebanon-UN-Withdrawal)
