<HEADLINE> S. Korea Asks Mongolia to Support Peace on Korean Peninsula </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, June 19 (Xinhua) -- South Korean ambassador to
Mongolia, Choi Yon Chul, has asked the Mongolian government and
people to support reconciliation on the Korean Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
"I hope that Mongolian people and government will pay more
attention to and support the reconciliation process of the two
Koreas," Choi told the Mongolian Daily newspaper on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"We will continue sticking to 'Sunshine' policy, and the
support from all over the world is very important for
consolidating peace on the Korean peninsula."
</P>
<P>
Choi said the signing of the joint declaration by leaders of
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) and South Korean
during the Inter-Korean summit last week, had become a historical
event for the reconciliation on the Korean Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The wide-ranging agreement not only can ease tension on the
Korean Peninsula but also can promote reconciliation, economic
ties, reunions of separated families and realize peaceful
reunification, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
