<HEADLINE> Australian PM to Visit India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Australian Prime Minister John
Howard will pay an official visit to India on July 10 and 11 this
year, the Indian External Affairs Ministry announced here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Howard's visit, the first official visit to India by an
Australian prime minister since 1989, is intended to "further
advance Australian-Indian cooperation in all respects," an
official release of the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
During his visit Howard will have contacts with the Indian
president, vice president, prime minister and other senior
government ministers, the release added.
</P>
<P>
It noted that in 1999 Australia's total trade with India
amounted to 2.1 billion U.S. dollars and its investments in India
are currently estimated at more than 1 billion dollars. 
</P>
