<HEADLINE> 15 Killed in India-Controlled Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen people, including nine "
foreign mercenaries" and an army officer, have been killed in
India-controlled Jammu and Kashmir since Sunday evening, the Press
Trust of India (PTI) reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
In a major encounter in Hafruda forest in the frontier district
of Kupwara in north Kashmir, nine "foreign mercenaries" were shot
dead by troops which launched a massive combing operation in the
forest on Sunday evening to flush out militants, the PTI quoted a
Defense Ministry spokesman in Srinagar, capital of India-
controlled Jammu and Kashmir, as saying.
</P>
<P>
Militants opened heavy fire at the troops and in the ensuing
gun-battle, six militants were shot dead late Sunday night and
three more were killed early Monday, the spokesman told the PTI.
</P>
<P>
An army officer identified as Captain Subramanyam was seriously
injured in the encounter and died later in hospital, he added.
</P>
<P>
Elsewhere in India-controlled Jammu and Kashmir, four militants
and a village defense committee member were killed and a girl
injured in separate incidents since Sunday evening, the PTI added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
