<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops Shell Rebel Vehicles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Sunday fired artillery on Tamil rebels vehicles in the northern
Jaffna peninsula, killing or injuring at least 10 rebels, a
military spokesman said Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
He said a long-range army patrol observed two rebel vehicles
carrying some 35-40 rebels from Tanankilappu toward Pooreryn on
Sunday and troops directed artillery fire at the vehicles.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that due to artillery fire about 10 rebels were
killed or wounded, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Government troops also on Sunday destroyed a rebel bunker near
Kilaly area which lies on the southern stretch of the Jaffna
peninsula,killing two rebels, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels, who are fighting a war for a separate state
for minority Tamils in the north and east of the country, had
overrun several government military camps and captured some
territory on the peninsula until last month when the troops
successfully stalled a rebel push to recapture their former
stronghold. 
</P>
</TEXT>
