<HEADLINE> Albania to Host NATO Military Exercises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Five NATO members and nine
partnership countries are set to take part in military exercises
code-named Cooperative Dragon 2000, which begins on Wednesday in
Albania, NATO officials announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
The exercises will last for nearly two weeks until July 1.
</P>
<P>
The military game will be the largest in the Balkan region
launched by NATO this year. It is aimed at reaching consensus and
understanding in actions of military support and humanitarian aid,
the military game's information center said.
</P>
<P>
The five NATO members taking part are Greece, Italy, Turkey,
Britain and Hungary. The nine NATO partners are Albania,
Azerbaijan, Bulgaria, Macedonia, Georgia, Moldova, Romania,
Slovakia and Ukraine. 
</P>
