<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia's foreign trade showed
a deficit of 62.7 million U.S. dollars in the first five months of
the year, 51 percent higher than the figure of the same period
last year, reported the Mongolian National Statistical Office
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The total foreign trade in the said period amounted to 344.5
million dollars, of which exports accounted for 140.9 million
dollars and imports 203.6 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the same period of last year, the country
exported mainly mineral and livestock products and imported
automobiles, machinery, electric appliances and food. 
