<HEADLINE> Henan Province Hit by Locusts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan Province,
a major grain producer of China, is fighting a disastrous locust
plague.
</P>
<P>
So far, locusts and their eggs have been found in more than 250,
000 ha of farmland in 34 counties.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that a large number of locusts swarmed over the
province last summer and autumn, and the survivors have become a
threat this year. The climate and environment of the province are
ideal for locusts to thrive in.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has decided to spray pesticide from
the air over about 33,000 ha. Weather permitting, the work will
be finished by the end of June.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, manual spreading of pesticide is under way. 
</P>
</TEXT>
