<HEADLINE> Rain-fed Flood in Fujian Kills 19 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The recent rainstorms in coastal
Fujian Province have caused severe flooding, with the death toll
hitting 19 so far.
</P>
<P>
In the past two days, 35 counties in Fujian have had the daily
rainfall exceeding 100 mm, with that of Longhai County topping 380
mm, according to the provincial government.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 1,000 ha of farmland and more than 200 ha of fish ponds
in Xiamen have been flooded. The 19 deaths occurred in Quanzhou
and Zhangzhou cities during the collapse of houses and a landslide.
</P>
<P>
The local governments have been fully mobilized and are busy
tackling the floods. 
