Singh would hold wide-ranging talks with Putin, Russian Foreign
Minister Igor Ivanov and National Security Council Advisor Sergei
Ivanov on bilateral, regional and international issues of
bilateral concern and interest, the PTI quoted a senior official
with the Indian External Affairs Ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
The official also described the Indo-Russian relations as "time-
tested" and "broad-based," said the PTI.
</P>
<P>
New Delhi and Moscow are expected to sign a major declaration
on their strategic partnership during Putin's visit, scheduled for
the first 10 days of October. 
</P>
