reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The majority of issues that arose last year between Zambia and
Botswana, Lesotho, Namibia and Swaziland have been resolved, but
South Africa remains the major stumbling block, Zambian Commerce,
Trade and Industry Minister William Harrington said here at the
weekend.
</P>
