<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 19 (Xinhua) -- This China's largest metropolis
is set to control its population of permanent residents within 16
million by the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
Sources at a forum on population and family planning held here
today said the population of Shanghai citizens will be controlled
within 14 million, and the birth rate of permanent residents will
be targeted at 9.6 per thousand by that year.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is one of the biggest cities in China, with a large
number of migrants and a rapidly-aging population.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai municipal government has published a special
decision on the administration of population and family planning.
