<HEADLINE> China-made Air-Conditioners of High Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Some 96 percent of China-made air
conditioners are up to the required standard, according to a
report issued here today by the State Bureau of Quality and
Technical Supervision.
</P>
<P>
The bureau has conducted quality checks on over 25 brands of
air-conditioners produced by 24 enterprises in eight provinces and
municipalities, including Beijing, Shanghai and Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
Of the 25 brands, only one brand, with the trademark "Huiyang"
and produced by a Nanhai-based company in Guangdong Province, was
unqualified.
</P>
<P>
The report said the majority of air-conditioner manufacturers
in China have established quality control systems.
</P>
<P>
The report noted that the installation of air-conditioners also
affects their operation, and on March 1 the bureau enacted
provisions to regulate the fixing of air-conditioners.
</P>
<P>
The report also pointed out that air-conditioner manufacturers
in China rely too much on introducing foreign technologies.
</P>
<P>
There are some 70 air-conditioner makers in China, with a total
annual capacity of 22.5 million units.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, China produced more than 13 million air-conditioners,
making it one of the world's leading air-conditioner makers.
</P>
</TEXT>
