<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Most Chinese-Made Pressure Pots Qualified: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- An official survey conducted in
the first quarter of this year found that 91.3 percent of China-
made pressure pots are up to the required standards, according to
the State Quality and Technical Supervision Administration.
</P>
<P>
The administration published the results of the investigation
here today. It revealed that 87.5 percent of the domestic pressure
pots made of aluminum are of good quality, while 100 percent of
the pressure pots made of stainless steel passed the official
tests.
</P>
<P>
The stainless steel products, which are more stable in quality
and safer, are likely to take over the urban market from their
aluminum counterparts. Currently, stainless steel pressure pots
have a 20 percent share of the market.
</P>
<P>
The administration has urged the manufacturers to pay attention
to the quality of rubber seals, saying that poor quality rubber
seals are detrimental to human health.
</P>
<P>
Pressure pots used to be a headache for local quality
supervisors. In 1994, only 29 percent of the pressure pots
surveyed by the administration were up to standard. In 1997, the
percentage of qualified pressure pots reached 80.9, thanks to
efforts made by the departments concerned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
