<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sensex Breaches 4,800-Level on Bombay Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The Sensitive Index (Sensex)
rose on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) Monday, buoyed by
persistent support from operators and buying by foreign funds.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-30 share Sensitive Index opened firm at 4,808.25 and
immediately touched a low of 4,788.94.
</P>
<P>
However, a sudden buying spree took the Sensex to the day's
high of 4,884.89 before closing at 4,837.24 as against last Friday
's close of 4,764.67, showing a gain of 72.57 points or 1.52
percent.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 index also shot up by 52.84 points to 2,453.84 from
the previous close of 2,401.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 index and the Dollex were quoted sharply up at 526.
32 and 196.08 compared with the previous close of 515.53 and 191.8
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-500 index firmed up by 35.31 points to 1,597.02 from
last Friday's close of 1,561.71. 
</P>
</TEXT>
