<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 58 Found Dead in British Port Lorry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The bodies of 58 people were found
in the back of a lorry at the English port of Dover early on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the Dutch-registered lorry, which arrived from
Zeebrugge, Belgium, just before midnight, has been arrested.
</P>
<P>
The 54 men and four women presumably of oriental origins were
thought to have been illegal immigrants. A Home Office spokeswoman
told Xinhua that the identities and nationalities of the dead were
still unknown, and an investigation was under way.
</P>
<P>
Two survivors, both men, have been taken to hospital and have
not yet been questioned.
</P>
<P>
A Customs and Excise spokeswoman said the bodies were
discovered by a single officer during a routine search of the
lorry.
</P>
<P>
So far, there was no official statement on the cause of death.
The lorry was an airtight 18-meter-long container which was only
partially loaded with fresh tomatoes.
</P>
<P>
Its refrigerating unit was not switched on and it remains
unclear what the interior temperature would have been, said the
spokeswoman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
