<HEADLINE> China to Plant 46 Million Ha of Trees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- China plans to plant another 46
million ha of trees in the next 30 years, according to officials
here today.
</P>
<P>
Li Yucai, deputy director of the State Forestry Administration,
said at a national working conference on afforestation that
priority should be given to the upper reaches of the Yangtze and
Yellow rivers and regions surrounding Beijing.
</P>
<P>
He said that China will pay more attention to ecological
factors than economic returns in afforestation, and efforts will
be made to ensure a sound eco-system in the west, as China is
preparing to boost the economy of its western regions.
</P>
<P>
The country will also solicit overseas help in afforestation
and encourage private investment in the field as well, the
official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
