<HEADLINE> ADB Pledges Enough Funds for Grain Purchase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The China Agricultural Development
Bank (ADB) has pledged to offer enough funds for the government to
purchase grain from farmers without having to issue IOUs.
</P>
<P>
As grain purchasing gets under way in some southern provinces,
the ADB is committing itself to providing sufficient loans to
local governments on time.
</P>
<P>
He Linxiang, president of the ADB, urged the local branches to
step up extension of loans to facilitate the grain purchase.
</P>
<P>
The ADB has extended a total of 315.94 billion yuan in the past
two years for the purchase of grain, cotton and edible oil.
</P>
