<HEADLINE> PLA Chief of General Staff Meets Japanese Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Fu Quanyou, chief of the General
Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA), met here
today with Yuji Fujinawa, chairman of the Council of Joint Chiefs
of Staff of the Self-Defense Forces of Japan.
</P>
<P>
Fu, also a member of the Central Military Commission, said that
China and Japan are neighboring countries, and developing Sino-
Japanese friendship is the common aspiration of the two peoples,
although the two countries have endured an unfortunate history.
</P>
<P>
He said that under the guidance of the Sino-Japanese friendly
and cooperative partnership devoted to peace and development,
which was established by the leaders of the two countries, the
bilateral relations have enjoyed smooth development.
</P>
<P>
On the Taiwan issue, he said that the One-China stance of the
Chinese government is consistent, firm and clear. He voiced his
hope that the Japanese side, proceeding from the strategic height
and in the spirit of learning from history and facing the future,
would resolve the problems left over by history and the Taiwan
issue, properly.
</P>
<P>
Yuji Fujinawa said that Japan will deal with the problems
between the two countries properly, and is willing to make
unremitting efforts to develop Japanese-Chinese relations.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the meeting, a ceremony was held to welcome the
Japanese guests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
