<HEADLINE> Diplomats to China Visit Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Diplomats to China from 11 Latin
American and Caribbean countries are currently visiting east China
's Shandong province.
</P>
<P>
The envoys arrived here on June 17 for a five-day visit to the
province.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with the envoys yesterday, Wu Guanzheng, a
member of the Political Bureau of China's Communist Party (CPC)
Central Committee and secretary of the CPC Shandong Provincial
Committee, encouraged both sides to further tap the potential in
bilateral cooperation. He said both sides share strong
complementarity in social and economic developments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
