<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Leading Officials, Their Families Urged to Be Honest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese Party leader has
reminded leading officials to be honest and law-abiding and not to
involve family members in any illegal activities.
</P>
<P>
Wei Jianxing, a member of the Standing Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee Political Bureau,
made the call during a trip in southwestern Yunnan Province from
June 13-18. During the week, Wei visited local factories and
villages.
</P>
<P>
In talks with local officials, Wei emphasized the importance of
CPC General Secretary Jiang Zemin's recent instructions on the
Party roles, calling for firmly fighting against corrupt elements
and waste of people's money because of dereliction of duty.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that in recent years, some middle- and high-
level leading officials have used their power to benefit their
spouses and children. The problem has become acute and ordinary
people are voicing their complaints.
</P>
<P>
He said it is right that the central government has banned
spouses and children of officials from engaging in businesses
within the domination scope of the officials.
</P>
<P>
Leading officials or their family members who violate the rules
must be punished, he warned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
