<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar's weekend
spike to its highest level in more than two months was reversed in
a session of profit taking on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The local currency neared 61 U.S. cents Friday night as the
weaker-than-expected data out in the United States reinforced
hopes that the interest rate differential between Australia and
the United States would not blow out.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar finished the local session at 60.28 U.S.
cents, from 60.71 at the end of the local session Friday.
</P>
<P>
During the day, the unit traded between 60.19 and 60.71 U.S.
cents.
</P>
<P>
Also at the close, the Australian dollar was at 0.6235 euro
from 0.6385 at Friday's close and 63.8 Japanese yen from 64.67.
</P>
