<HEADLINE> Turkey to Host 6th International Handball Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth International Open
Handball Tournament will be held in Alanya, Turkey's southern
Antalya province from June 26 to July 1, the Anatolia News Agency
said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ramazan Demirci, Chairman of the Handball Coaches' Association
and General Coordinator of the Sixth International Alanya Open
Handball Tournament, told reporters on Monday that 130 teams will
participate in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
"We are very pleased to host 2,000 Turkish and foreign
sportsmen, referees and administrators," he added.
</P>
<P>
Alanya, which lies on the coast of the Mediterranean Sea, is a
Turkish tourist resort famous for its natural beauties, culture
and history. 
</P>
