<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 8848.net Signs Deal with SETC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai-based 8848.net, China
's largest on-line retailer, clinched a deal on Monday with the
State Economic and Trade Commission (SETC) to build e-commerce
platform for Chinese enterprises, according to the "China Economic
Times".
</P>
<P>
This is the first cooperative deal between a domestic Internet
company and a government department.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the Economic Information Center under SETC
and 8848.net will share resources by opening two windows on the
CHINABBC.com of SETC and the 8848.net.
</P>
<P>
The Economic Information Center will help Chinese enterprises
access information from these windows while 8848.net will provide
needed technology.
</P>
<P>
Xiang Xin, deputy director of SETC's market department, noted
that 8848.net has a wealth of experience in market exploration,
technological development and management. The cooperation will
facilitate Chinese enterprises to develop faster by utilizing e-
commerce platform.
</P>
<P>
Tan Zhi, president of 8848.net, said that the two sides worked
hard to set up the initial establishment of the enterprise
platform in three months. They will then choose more large
enterprises for trial operation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
