<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Twenty Chinese Entrepreneurs Honored in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Twenty Chinese Mainland
entrepreneurs received the 2000 Bauhinia Outstanding Entrepreneur
Awards here Monday for their contribution to the advancement of
commerce, industry, science and technology.
</P>
<P>
The awards are aimed to recognize outstanding entrepreneurs
from the township and private sector enterprises on the Chinese
mainland and to provide an excellent opportunity for entrepreneurs
from Hong Kong and the mainland to share the experience of success,
said Poon Chung-kwong, president of the Hong Kong Polytechnic
University, organizer of the event.
</P>
<P>
"As China is expected to joint the World Trade Organization and
with the increasing business opportunities brought forth by
electronic commerce, I believe that economic activities between
Hong Kong and the interior of China will be more frequent than
ever before," Poon said.
</P>
<P>
To qualify for the awards, the candidates' enterprises must
have a gross production or business value of over 100 million RMB
(12 million U.S. dollars), with an annual growth rate of more than
20 percent over the past three years.
</P>
<P>
The winners include Duan Yongji, chairman of the Stone Group
Corporation, and Zhang Benzheng, president of Tsing Hua
Unisplendor Corporation Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The township and private enterprises are playing an important
role in China's economy. Statistics indicate that currently the
township and private enterprises account for nearly a half of
China's gross domestic product. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
