<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Ready to Celebrate SAR's 3rd Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG June 19 (Xinhua) -- The Home Affairs Bureau will
organize two major celebration activities to mark the third
anniversary of the establishment of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
To encourage community participation in celebrating the
anniversary, the bureau, in conjunction with the Leisure and
Cultural Services Department, will hold a community concert in the
evening on July 1 at the Hong Kong Coliseum.
</P>
<P>
The concert will feature the world famous China Symphony
Orchestra Chorus, the Hong Kong Chinese Orchestra, the Hong Kong
Children's Choir, and local celebrity Roman Tam.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, members of the public are also welcome to
attend the flag-raising ceremony which will start at 8 a.m. at the
Bauhinia Square outside the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center to mark the anniversary. Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa and
over 500 guests, including senior government officials,
dignitaries and community leaders, will attend the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
A choir drawn from two schools will for the first time sing the
National Anthem during the ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
