<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Economics Book Shares Views of U.S. Scholars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- A collection of interviews with
American economics scholars has been published in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
"In Search of Wisdom -- Interviews with MIT (Massachusetts
Institute of Technology) and Harvard Scholars of Economics and
Management Science," released by the Beijing University Publishing
House, was written over a two-year period by three Chinese
students who studied at MIT.
</P>
<P>
The interviews cover timely topics in economics and management
including issues in the world economy, the Asian financial crisis,
IT and reorganization of China's enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Nobel Prize owners including Paul Samuelson and Franco
Modigliani, presented their unique views on China's economic
reform and development in the book.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Shuguang, a researcher of Chinese Academy of Social
Sciences, said that the book provides a global view on world
economics and management sciences, as well as guidelines for China
's reform and development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
