<HEADLINE> CPPCC Leader on Strategy of Developing West </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The strategy to develop China's
western regions is a long-term and complicated one and should be
carried out in a planned and systematic manner.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), made these
remarks today at the 22nd meeting of the chairman and vice
chairmen of the National Committee of the CPPCC.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was held for preparing the upcoming 10th meeting of
the Standing Committee of the CPPCC National Committee which will
focus on developing China's west. Li hailed the strategy as being
of great importance to the development of both western and eastern
regions of China, as well as to the sustainable economic and
social development of the whole country.
</P>
<P>
Since April, the CPPCC National Committee has sent several
groups to conduct inspection tours to western provinces and held
discussion panels with experts and scholars, according to Zheng
Wantong, secretary-general of the CPPCC National Committee.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also listened to a report on the recent "21st
Century Forum--2000 Conference". 
</P>
</TEXT>
