<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) finished 16.02 points
lower at 1,996.18 points in thin trading.
</P>
<P>
The volume totaled 286.65 million units worth 395.75 million
Singapore dollars (about 232.11 million U.S. dollars). Declining
issues outnumbered advancers by 190 to 103 with 250 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Adroit topped the volume list as it registered a turnover of 66.
33 million units. It was followed by AddvalTech which had 18.90
million units traded. Kyosha was the next with 13.81 million
counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Jade Tech was the biggest gainer of the day skyrocketing by 194
cents to close at 2.93 Singapore dollars. Datacrft finished the
day 30 cents higher at 8.50 U.S. dollars. SPH 100 edged up 20
cents to end at 26.80 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
CenProp topped the losers of the day incurring a big loss of
200 cents and closing at 14.00 Singapore dollars. Creative 50
dropped 130 cents to finish at 43.50 Singapore dollars. SIA 200
and Venture retreated 50 cents to end at 16.80 and 18.10 Singapore
dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
Brokers attributed today's slump to lackluster sentiment and
low liquidity which gave the market little impetus to move upward.
</P>
<P>
They believed in words from the U.S that investors will be held
hostage by interest-rate concern ahead of the U.S. Federal
Reserves rate decision on June 28.  
</P>
</TEXT>
