<HEADLINE> More Foreign Tourists Flock to S. Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 19 (Xinhua) -- A total of 472,849 foreigners
visited South Korea in May, a 18.5 percent rise from the same
month of last year, the Korea National Tourism Organization said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The May figure, which was also a record monthly high, brought
the total number of foreign tourists in the first five months of
this year to 2.15 million, a 17.29 percent growth over the same
time last year.
</P>
<P>
Of the tourist figure in May, the number of Chinese visitors
rose 51 percent from the year before and that of Japanese
increased 15.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The organization attributed the sharp increase in Asian
tourists to the steady economic recovery of the region which
suffered a financial crisis in late 1997.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to increased number of foreign tourists, the state-run
organization was quite optimistic that this year's goal of
attracting 5.1 million foreign tourists will be easily met.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
