<HEADLINE> Klim Breaks Short Course Swimming World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Michael Klim of Australia broke
the world short course record for the men's 50 meters butterfly on
the weekend.
</P>
<P>
Klim was timed at 23.11 seconds, 0.08 seconds faster than the
previous world mark set by Lars Frolander of Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Klim, world champion at the 100 meters butterfly, set the new
world mark in a special time trial at the Australian Institute of
Sport in Canberra. 
</P>
