<HEADLINE> Top Leaders Offer Condolences for Death of Head of Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Top Chinese leaders, including
Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan, Hu Jintao, Wei
Jianxing and Li Lanqing, have expressed their condolences for the
death of Yun Bulong, chairman of the People's Government of the
Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The Inner Mongolia leader, a member of the Central Committee of
the Communist Party of China (CPC), was killed in a car accident
on June 12, while making an inspection visit to Xilin Gol League
of the autonomous region. He was 62.
</P>
<P>
Yun, an ethnic Mongolian, was born in December 1937. In 1962,
after graduating from the Taiyuan Engineering Institute, he worked
in a heavy machinery plant in Taiyuan.
</P>
<P>
He became a vice-chairman of the regional government in 1992
and took over as the chairman of the regional government in 1998.
</P>
