<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Development Zone Reports High Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 19 (Xinhua) -- High growth during the first five
months this year has enabled the Tianjin Development Zone to
maintain its position as the fastest-growing development zone in
China.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that the zone realized 9.8 billion yuan
in gross domestic product (GDP) during the five-month period, an
increase of 20 percent over the same 1999 period. Industrial added-
value in the zone grew 21.6 percent to 7.09 billion yuan. Export
turnover in the zone totaled 1.26 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The zone's four pillar industries, namely electronics and
telecommunications, light industry, medicine and machinery,
continued to be a driving force behind the zone's economy.
</P>
<P>
A total 3,262 overseas-funded ventures have been approved in
the development zone so far, attracting 12.58 billion US dollars
in total investment. More than 200 multinational companies have
landed in the zone, investing more than six billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government took the initiative in 1994 to set up
economic and technological development zones in 14 of its coastal
cities, a practice that has already expanded to all major
industrial cities in the nation including those in inland areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
