<DOCNO> XIE20000619.0200 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand, S. Korea to Hold Talks on Free Trade Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Thailand will soon negotiate with
South Korea on a plan to set up a free trade area between the two
countries, as the Republic of Korea (South Korea) and the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea have tentatively reached a
historic agreement on unification, The Thai News Agency (TNA)
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Director-General of the Department of Export Promotion of the
Commerce Ministry Banpot Hongtong was quoted as saying that the
Commerce Ministry through the Department of Business Economics was
studying the feasibility of establishing a free trade area between
Thailand and South Korea.
</P>
<P>
The plan would be possible if South Korea eliminated measures
hindering Thai exports to the republic, including tariff barriers,
import restrictions, and strict sanitary inspections, particularly
on agricultural products, he said.
</P>
<P>
Thai authorities will negotiate with their South Korean
counterparts on more opening up of South Korean market for Thai
farm products in exchange for the Thai government's investment
incentives and technological transfer for South Korean enterprises,
which will pave the way for an agreement on free trade area
between the two countries, Banpot disclosed.
</P>
<P>
It was likely that South Korea would accept the Thai proposal,
as food and other agricultural products were significant for the
economic stability in South Korea, projected the senior Commerce
Ministry official.
</P>
<P>
South Korea is reportedly considering concluding free trade
area agreements with the United States, Japan, Chile and Thailand.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
