<HEADLINE> Manila Vows to Increase Job Opportunities in Countryside </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government will
strive hard to provide rural residents enough employment and
livelihood opportunities in a bid to spur economic growth and
increase their incomes, the Philippine News Agency said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Vice Chairman Donna Gasgonia of the National Anti-Poverty
Commission (NAPC) was quoted as saying that this aims to stop and
eventually reverse the trend of rural folk flocking to crowded
urban centers to seek employment.
</P>
<P>
"We are reversing the trend. We know the poor are concentrated
in the rural areas, so we are focusing our assistance there
instead of in the cities," Gasgonia said.
</P>
<P>
With government assistance, the NAPC, which is chaired by
President Joseph Estrada, hopes to help residents in the
countryside generate their own employment by starting their own
businesses, Gasgonia said.
</P>
<P>
Secretary Horacio Morales of the Department of Agrarian Reform
(DAR) was also reported as saying that President Estrada has
thrown his full support behind food security through agricultural
modernization as his administration's primary weapon against
poverty.
</P>
<P>
Food security is one of the Estrada administration's five
centerpiece programs, alongside peace and order, mass housing, the
fight against graft and corruption, and electoral reforms.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
