<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WFP Provides Food Aid to Eastern Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The World Food Program (WFP) has
sent a first consignment of 350 tons of maize meal to the
Kisangani station after receiving a request for 1,500 tons from
the WFP Kisangani mother office in Kinshasa, the New Vision
newspaper reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Food demands in Kisangani from international aid agencies have
increased sharply following the six-day clashes between Ugandan
and Rwandan troops in the northeast city of the Democratic
Republic of Congo, the report said.
</P>
<P>
"We have just been asked to increase the food dispatches to
Eastern Congo and we are organizing the food for them. Some of the
food is bought here and some is got from Mombasa," said Alvira
Ferreira, WFP Uganda head of Reporting Section.
</P>
<P>
"By our calculations, if given other supplements, 1,500 tons
should be enough for 100,000 people for about a month," she said,
adding that "somewhere at the end of last month they asked for 630
tons, so this request is a sharp increase." 
</P>
</TEXT>
