<DOCNO> XIE20000619.0213 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SW China Province Improves Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The environment in southwest China
's Yunnan Province has been improved, according to a latest
government bulletin.
</P>
<P>
According to the bulletin, although 11 percent of lakes in the
province are getting worse, 23.5 percent have improved their
quality of water in the past year.
</P>
<P>
Some famous tourist attractions like the Erhai Lake, the Luguhu
Lake and the Fuxianhu Lake are so clean that their water can be
directly used as drinking water sources, the bulletin said.
</P>
<P>
The upper reaches of the province's major rivers have been
prevented from pollution. Air quality in 59 percent of the
province's cities reported 1st or 2nd class air quality.
</P>
<P>
The province also set up two new nature reserves in the past
year, adding the province's total number of nature reserves up to
112.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan received more than 37 million domestic and international
visitors last year, making it the No.1 tourist destinations in
western China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
