<DOCNO> XIE20000619.0215 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinjiang Launches State-Level Economic Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The state-level Shihezi Economic
and Technological Development Zone was inaugurated today in the
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, northwest China.
</P>
<P>
Li Shuxian, director of the administrative committee of the
zone, said that the zone will focus on the development of the
textiles industry, high-tech industries such as bio-chemistry,
chemicals and information, and equipment manufacturing based on
electronics and microelectronics industries.
</P>
<P>
Prior to 1992, when the work on the zone began, the area was an
important base of agriculture and animal husbandry, and light
industries in Xinjiang.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the gross domestic product, industrial
added value and revenue of the zone all increased at a rate of 40
percent annually over the past seven years.
</P>
<P>
The Shihezi Zone is located in the economic belt on the
northern slope of the Tianshan Mountain, a major economic
development zone in Xinjiang. 
</P>
</TEXT>
