<HEADLINE> 2 Killed, 7 Wounded in Shoot-out in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed, seven
others wounded, when alleged rebels of the Moro Islamic Liberation
Front (MILF ) figured in a shoot-out with an army sergeant in
north Mindanao Sunday night, Philippine News Agency (PNA) said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Local police chief Bernardo Vasquez was quoted as saying that
the dead and wounded were all local residents.
</P>
<P>
The shoot-out occurred after 7:00 p.m. Sunday when local army
sergeant Valentin Caluton went home from a night duty, Vasquez
added.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigation disclosed that Caluton was attacked by
six unidentified "Maranaos" or local tribesmen who reportedly
mauled him while walking along a street in Cagayan De Oro city,
Misamis Oriental province in north Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
Police said they could not ascertain the owner of the pistol
but were certain that the firearm was fired from an unknown gunman.
</P>
<P>
Investigators are not discounting reports about the possible
involvement of MILF rebels in the shoot-out since some witnesses
alleged that "Maranaos" are actually armed with high caliber
firearms such as M-16 and M-14 rifles.
</P>
<P>
This came after intelligence reports that a number of MILF
rebels who abandoned their camps in the Lanao provinces have taken
refuge with "Maranao" relatives in Cagayan de Oro, the PNA said.
</P>
</TEXT>
