<HEADLINE> Girl Abducted, Raped for 5 Days in N. Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- A couple from a north Philippine
town has sought local police help for the arrest of three men who
abducted their 13-year old daughter and took turns in abusing her
for five days, Philippine News Agency (PNA) said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The call for help came from the couple living in a village of
Bayambang in Pangasinan province shortly after their daughter was
abducted in a local town Basista on June 8, the PNA said.
</P>
<P>
The couple sought the arrest of the three abductors, all
allegedly local residents of Bayambang, who reportedly dragged the
little girl to a waiting tricycle on June 8.
</P>
<P>
This allegedly happened at the tricycle parking area in Basista
from where the victim passed through on her way to the Basista
Public Market to buy a short pant.
</P>
<P>
The girl was found five days later in a third place called
Malasiqui, dazed and in a state of shock. Through the help of a
passer-by, she was able to return home.
</P>
<P>
The girl said the suspects also forced her to drink a liquid
placed in a soft drink which caused her to have abnormal feelings.
While in that state, her abductors repeatedly abused her.
</P>
<P>
The victim has been brought to the Pangasinan Provincial
Hospital by her parents where doctors confirmed her ordeal from
the hands of her abductors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
