<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bronze Statue Stolen In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 19 (Xinhua) -- A 600-kg bronze statue of a
telephone girl was stolen recently in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Two lovers had arranged to meet by the statue, but when they
arrived they was no telephone girl at all.
</P>
<P>
The missing 1.7-meter-tall bronze statue is located in Huanghai
Road, one of the most crowded business centers in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The stolen statue was one of many sculptures the Shanghai city
authorities had erected in downtown streets. So far no clues to
the case have been found.
</P>
<P>
The sculptor, He Yong, wants to try his hand again at another
telephone girl.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Yonghao, chairman of the Shanghai Urban Sculptors'
Committee, called on the whole society to care for artistic pieces
and be vigilant against theft.
</P>
</TEXT>
