<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hefei to Become Modern Metropolis in 10 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Hefei, capital of east China's Anhui
Province near Shanghai, plans to become a modern metropolis in 10
years.
</P>
<P>
According to a development plan, which has been approved by the
State Council, more trees and grass will be planted in Hefei to
make it a garden city, covering 21.2 percent of local land areas.
</P>
<P>
Hefei, which is approved to develop 150 square kilometers for
the center of it, will give priority to the development of high-
tech and service sectors.
</P>
<P>
The city is expected to become an important educational base
and a major communications hub of the country, and a key
industrial base in the Yangtze River valley.  
</P>
</TEXT>
