<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seven Killed in Gas Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Seven people have been confirmed
dead during a weekend gas explosion in central China's Henan
Province.
</P>
<P>
Another four people were injured when the gas explosion broke
out at Yusong Coal Mine in Dengfeng at about six p.m. on June 17.
Thirteen of the 23 coal miners working underground at the time
were rescued while another seven are still missing.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident was still under investigation.
</P>
</TEXT>
