<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shandong Wants Overseas Funds for All Key Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Shandong Province in east China is
looking for overseas investment in all of its important and large-
scale construction projects, according to provincial governor Li
Chunting.
</P>
<P>
He told a meeting here recently that the introduction of more
overseas funds to major projects will be the key to helping the
province open wider to the outside world, adding that greater
efforts should be made on absorbing funds from major transnational
companies.
</P>
<P>
"We welcome those companies to set up manufacturing centers,
research and development centers and operation centers, as well as
regional headquarters in Shandong," he added.
</P>
<P>
Located on China's east coast, Shandong is the third-largest
economic powerhouse in the country after Guangdong and Shanghai.
</P>
</TEXT>
