<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Construction of Expressways Going Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- A key 2,272-meter tunnel of the
Ningbo-Taizhou-Wenzhou expressway in east China's Zhejiang
province has been completed, with a total investment of 50 million
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The first expressway going across the north of Guangdong
province, also part of the national-level Beijing-Zhuhai
expressway has almost been completed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the construction of Xuchang-Pingdingshan-Nanyang
expressway in central China's Henan province has also started. The
four-lane 163.5-km way, with a total investment of 3.5 billion
yuan, is expected to be finished in three years.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China's expressway had exceeded 10,000
kilometers by the end of 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
