<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Expansion of Two Major Ports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The expansion of China's two major
ports of Xiamen and Shenzhen, has recorded steady growth in the
last two months, according to the "China Shipping Weekly".
</P>
<P>
The port of Xiamen in east China's Fujian province has started
to build a shipping channel which will be able to carry 100,000-
ton ships. The project, with a total investment of 58 million yuan,
is expected to be finished in one year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the construction of a container dock at Shenzhen
Yantian Port, with a total investment of 3.9 billion Hong Kong
dollars, has already been completed. The project will have an
annual handling capacity of 1.2 million TEUs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
