<HEADLINE> B747-400s Planes for Sino-American Cargo Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- China Southern Airlines will
introduce two B747-400 cargo planes on its Sino-American air route,
according to the "China Air Transport Weekly".
</P>
<P>
The airlines opened the cargo service between Shenzhen and
Chicago in April, using B747-200 planes, which are able to fully
load 90-ton cargo each. The service will run three times a week.
</P>
<P>
B747-400 cargo planes, can load 30 more tons of cargo and
consume less oil, compared to B747-200 planes,said president Yan
Zhiqing.
</P>
<P>
Air China also intends to open Sino-American cargo service.
</P>
</TEXT>
