<HEADLINE> Cross-Straits Shipping Exchange Association Has New Leadership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The Cross-Straits Shipping
Exchange Association, under the Ministry of Communications, has
recently elected its new leadership.
</P>
<P>
According to the "China Shipping Weekly", Hu Hanxiang, director
of the shipping department attached to the ministry, was elected
new council director of the association and Zhang Junlei has
become the new secretary-general.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that under the new leadership, the association will
carry on the "one China" principle, promote cross-straits
transportation and contribute to national reunification.  
</P>
