<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Community Offers On-line Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Two minutes after sending an e-
mail message to a real estate management company complaining that
his tap needed fixing, a resident of Huilongguan Community,
northern Beijing received an online answer.
</P>
<P>
The reply came from the Tianhong Group, a community real estate
management company, saying that a repairman would be available in
a few hours, and asking the man to stay at home.
</P>
<P>
The online complaint service is the first of its kind in China,
according to China Youth Daily.
</P>
<P>
In addition to requesting home repairs, residents may gripe
about their monthly fees for property maintenance. An on-line
supermarket is also available and residents can enjoy home
delivery free of charge. A chatroom is open for residents to get
to know other people in their community.
</P>
<P>
Hu Rui, chief engineer with Tianhong Group, said the online
services make interactive realty management possible.
</P>
<P>
"Residents are able to apply for services any time. They don't
have to worry about the tight schedule of our company any more,"
he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
