<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earthquake Rocks Northern Philippine City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.7 on the
Richter scale shook the cities of San Fernando and Baguio in the
northern Philippines Monday, but no damage was reported, the
Philippine Institute of Volcanology and Seismology (Phivolcs) said.
</P>
<P>
In a preliminary report, the institute said the epicenter of
the earthquake was located at 28 kilometers northeast of San
Fernando City.
</P>
<P>
The tremor that is also registered at Intensity 5 in Baguio
City occurred at 9:59 a.m. local time (01:59 GMT) and more
aftershocks are expected, the institute said.
</P>
<P>
Cesario Salvador, seismologist of the Phivolcs station in
Baguio said the quake was stronger than last Wednesday's tremor
registered at Intensity 3 in Baguio.
</P>
<P>
Seismologists say the Phivolcs is still gathering data about
the quake from its various stations in Northern Luzon.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines is hit by an average of six earthquakes every
day but most are too weak to be felt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
