<HEADLINE> Beijingers Seek Better Housing, Education and Higher Income </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Better housing conditions, good
education for children and higher income top the list of Beijing
residents' concerns, according to a sample survey made public here
today.
</P>
<P>
The survey, conducted among 500 Beijingers by Beijing Home
Economics Research Society, shows that 25.3 percent of the
respondents want their living conditions improved when asked what
they needed most.
</P>
<P>
The result shows that more than 24 percent of the respondents
are in pursuit of higher incomes, 17.9 percent are seeking better
education and job opportunities for their children, while another
12.9 percent prefer to have more time to enjoy themselves. 
