<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Investment Grows Faster in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The growth rate of China's
investment in fixed assets increased to 9.5 percent year-on-year
by the end of May, compared with a 9.3 percent growth by the end
of April.
</P>
<P>
Figures released today by the National Bureau of Statistics
show that fixed assets' investment totaled 523.3 billion yuan in
the first five months of the year.
</P>
<P>
Infrastructure investment grew by 4.4 percent over the same
period last year to 291.1 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Investment in technological upgrading jumped by 19.8 percent to
93.9 billion yuan, and that in real estate maintained an growth
rate of 20.8 percent over the period, totaling 117.6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
More money was channeled to the central and western areas of
the country than to the east. Fixed assets' investment grew by 18.
4 percent and 13.7 percent respectively in central and western
China, compared with 9.1 percent in eastern China.
</P>
<P>
Investment in the central and western areas accounted for more
than one-third of the country's total. 
</P>
</TEXT>
