<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreman's Daughter Makes Boxing Debut with Knockout Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Freeda Foreman, daughter of
former heavyweight champion George Foreman, floored her opponent
with the first punch she landed, then knocked her out at 1:44 of
the second round in her boxing debut.
</P>
<P>
Her father refused to attend the bout in Las Vegas as he did
not want his daughter to begin a boxing career. He offered her 15,
000 U.S. dollars - the same amount as the purse for her first bout
- not to go into the ring.
</P>
<P>
Foreman, a 23-year-old former UPS worker from Greenville, South
Carolina, did not cash the check but went ahead Sunday as a pro at
Regent Las Vegas.
</P>
<P>
She knocked down LaQuanda Landers, a hairdresser from Milwaukee,
with a looping left in the opening seconds of the fight.
</P>
<P>
Landers, who also had not fought as a pro, was no match for
Foreman, who was hit only a couple of times before she trapped
Landers on the ropes in the second round and began pounding her.
Landers crumpled to the canvas and was counted out.
</P>
<P>
Foreman weighed 82 kilograms for the light heavyweight bout,
scheduled for four rounds of two minutes each, and Landers weighed
76 kilos.
</P>
<P>
In another debut by the daughter of a former heavyweight
champion, Maria Johansson of Sweden fought bravely but was
battered in a split decision loss to Karrie Frye, of LaPorte,
Indiana, in their super middleweight bout.
</P>
<P>
Johansson, a teacher and former bouncer whose father is Ingemar
Johansson, dropped to her knees after receiving an overhead right
in the second round. But Johansson, a 34-year-old mother of two,
regained her feet and was competitive the rest of the four-round
bout.
</P>
<P>
Two judges gave Frye the bout by scores of 39-36 and 40-35,
while one judge favored Johansson 38-37.
</P>
<P>
Johansson had her nose bloodied in the second round and had a
number of welts on her face by the end of the fight with Frye.
</P>
<P>
Johansson weighed 76 kilos while Frye 75 kilos. 
</P>
</TEXT>
