<DOCNO> XIE20000619.0310 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Seizes 1.3 Mln Stimulant Drug Tablets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities seized 1.3
million tablets of stimulant drugs early this month in Kengtung
township in the country's eastern Shan state, official newspaper
The New Light of Myanmar reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The seizure was jointly made by the local intelligence unit and
the police force when they searched a Hino bus at the Naungnoon
toll gate in the township on June 4.
</P>
<P>
The stimulants were uncovered in the wheel of the bus, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Three traffickers were arrested in connection with the case and
punishment is being given to them by the authorities under the
country's Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Law, the
report added.
</P>
<P>
Last month, nearly 2 million stimulant drug tablets were seized
in Myawaddy in the southeastern Kayin state, with six traffickers
arrested, according to an earlier report.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that in 1999, the Myanmar authorities
confiscated 28.75 million tablets of stimulant drugs along with 1,
447.55 kilos of opium and 272.94 kilos of heroin.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that stimulant drugs were first found
trafficked in Myanmar in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
