<HEADLINE> Jiangxi Gets First State-Level Economic Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The Nanchang Economic Development
Zone has been upgraded into a state-level economic zone, with
approval from the State Council.
</P>
<P>
This is the first national economic zone in this capital of
east China's Jiangxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Opened in 1992, the Nanchang Economic Development Zone covers 9.
8 sq. km. It has a complete set of infrastructure facilities, with
investors enjoying preferential policies.
</P>
