<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unmanned Car on Driving Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Changsha, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The fourth model of a China-made
unmanned car has recently passed a road test in the capital city
of Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
The car can perform all the normal functions that a driver
could do such as starting the ignition, changing gears and parking.
</P>
<P>
The latest unmanned car, the fourth-generation model, was
developed by the China National Defense Science and Technology
University after a five-year effort. The car is capable of running
at the maximum speed of 75.6 km/h.
</P>
<P>
The university started developing the first model of the car
in the 1980s.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
