<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Harbor Area in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
TIANJIN, June 19 (Xinhua) -- This north China port city has
basically completed the construction of a new harbor area covering
five sq. km.
</P>
<P>
The project involved a total investment of two billion yuan (
about 360 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The area has berths for petrochemicals, coke, non-metallic ore
and coal, and 12 warehouses.
</P>
<P>
The new harbor area will have a handling capacity of 20.5
million tons of cargo when it is completed next year.
</P>
<P>
Officials said the area will give an impetus to the
development of Tianjin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
