<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Following are the highlights of
today's major Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 People's Daily
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said during an interview with
the American magazine "Science" last month that the Chinese
Government will continue to increase investment in the basic
research and encourage the relevant agencies to support the basic
research.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said in the interview, which was carried in the latest
issue of "Science", that China will create a more favorable
research environment for scientists, and encourage scientists to
choose research subjects on their own and research institutes to
institute new mechanisms that suit the law of scientific
development.
</P>
<P>
-- Some 116 Chinese nationals evacuated from the Solomon
Islands arrived at Guangzhou's Beiyun Airport at Sunday afternoon
by a special plane of China Southern Airlines.
</P>
<P>
Political instability, starting June 4, has caused chaos in the
Solomon Islands. The Chinese government has taken immediate
measures to evacuate the Chinese nationals there, following the
suit of many other countries.
</P>
<P>
Xinhua Daily Telegraph
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji has stressed that construction
quality is the essential part of the Three Gorges Project.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Ninth Plenary Session of the Three Gorges
Project Construction Committee under the State Council, the
premier urged the builders to step up environmental protection and
ecological construction in the dam area and do a good job in the
resettlement of local people.
</P>
<P>
-- More than six billion yuan will be used in the next ten years
to protect the Chinese capital from sandstorms, according to the
State Forestry Administration.
</P>
<P>
The government will put the protection of Beijing as its top
priority in its battle against sandstorms and desertification. The
protected zone will cover an area of 260,000 sq km, involving 84
counties around Beijing and neighboring cities.
</P>
<P>
 China Daily
</P>
<P>
-- President Jiang Zemin said that he hopes all young people,
Chinese and foreign, the scientists and scholars around the world
will make the best use of the Internet, but be on guard against
negative impacts of the net.
</P>
<P>
-- The Chinese Ministry of Agriculture promised that locusts
will be brought under control within the next two months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
