<HEADLINE> Hewitt Wins London Grass Court Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Australian Lleyton Hewitt defeated
six times Wimbledon champion Pete Sampras of the United States 6-4,
6-4 to win the London grass court men's tennis tournament on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Australian, nine years younger than Sampras, has announced
himself as a serious contender for Wimbledon after the victory.
</P>
<P>
"I got off to good start and that's the best I've ever returned.
</P>
<P>
"It was fantastic. Not to drop a set (all tournament) is great
preparation going into Wimbledon. I was seeing the ball out there
like a football," he said.
</P>
<P>
Sampras struggled on his forehand and had no answer as Hewitt
out-aced him nine to five and produced some wonderful service
return winners.
</P>
<P>
It was Hewitt's fourth ATP title of the year, his sixth in all,
and gave him revenge for his three-set loss against Sampras, whom
he had never previously beaten, in the Queen's semifinals last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
