<HEADLINE> Raymond Wins Edgbaston Women's Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- American doubles specialist Lisa
Raymond defeated Tamarine Tanasugarn of Thailand to win the
Edgbaston women's tennis tournament in Birmingham on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Raymond, who dismissed third seed Jennifer Capriati and top
seed Nathalie Tauziat, beat the Thai outsider 6-2, 6-7 and 6-4 in
the final.
</P>
<P>
The American cruised to the opening set in a flurry of aces but
let her concentration slip in the second as Tanasugarn, who
reached the fourth round at last year's Wimbledon, showed her
pedigree on the grass surface.
</P>
<P>
The number six seed eventually lost the set during a close
fought tie-break and received a code violation when she sent a
ball spiralling over in the grandstand in frustration.
</P>
<P>
The deciding set went with serve but Raymond's impressive
service game and mixed array of groundshots finally overcame the
determined Tanasugarn in the 10th game.
</P>
<P>
Despite a host of doubles triumphs, including last year's
Wimbledon mixed crown with Leander Paes, Raymond had previously
won only one singles tour title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
