<HEADLINE> Italian Wins Stage, Spaniard Leads Overall in Tour of Calunya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Breaking away from the main group
46 kilometers after the start, Italian Gabriele Missaglia won the
fourth stage of the Tour of Catalunya cycle race on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Missaglia got off a group of 42 riders on the steep descent
from Alt Orrius, 46 km into the 158.4 km section, in a time of
three hours 38 minutes and 15 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Overall leader Marcos Serrano of Spain stayed in the main bunch
which lagged far behind. He now led the overall standings with an
accumulated time of 11:50:45.
</P>
<P>
His ONCE teammate and compatriot David Canada took charge of
the race. He led fellow Spaniard Santiago Blanco of Vitalicio by
two seconds in the overall time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
