<HEADLINE> Colombia Discovers New Oil Field </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, June 19 (Xinhua)-- A consortium of Colombian,
Brazilian and Canadian companies discovered a petroleum field with
reserves believed above 200 million barrels in Colombia,
President of Colombian Petroleum Company (Ecopetrol) Alberto
Calderon Zuleta said Monday.
</P>
<P>
"This is the third most important oilfield discovered in
Colombia in the last 20 years after Cusiana-Cupiagua and Cano
Limon, and removes possibilities of importing petroleum again,"
indicated the Ecopetrol official.
</P>
<P>
Ecopetrol is participating with a 50 percent of investments and
earnings from this oilfield; Petrobras of Brazil, with 25 percent;
and Canadian of Canada, with another 25 percent. Operator of the
Association's Contract is the Brazilian company.
</P>
<P>
Colombia produces nowadays 700,000 barrels per day (bpd), which
are the national economy's main product, with an income from
exports calculable for this year of high prices, at about 5
billion dollars. In 1999, production was 800,000 bpd.  
</P>
</TEXT>
