<HEADLINE> European Leading Stocks Close Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Europe's leading stock markets
closed mixed Monday, as weak financial stocks left the blue-chip
index in London narrowly down while Frankfurt and Paris posted
modest gains.
</P>
<P>
London's benchmark FTSE 100 index ended down 35.8 points or 0.
55 percent at 6490.2. Heavyweight telecom and banking components
lost ground, with Vodafone AirTouch losing more than 4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Amid a weak financial sector, Halifax, Britain's biggest
mortgage lender, lost 2.3 percent and Barclays closed 2.4 percent
lower.
</P>
<P>
Heavyweight oil and gas shares helped to limit the FTSE 100's
fall with BP Amoca up 1 percent. Electronics and engineering firm
Invensys topped the list of FTSE 100 gainers with a 5.6 percent
advance.
</P>
<P>
The pan-European FTSE Eurotop 300 closed 0.47 percent lower at
1609.38, with its telecom sub-index down 2 percent and banks down
1 percent.
</P>
<P>
German shares closed firmly, with chemical stocks and insurers
leading the gainers. The benchmark Dax 30 index closed 67.40 or 0.
95 percent higher at 7198.8.
</P>
<P>
In Paris, the CAC 40 blue chip index ended up 48.9 or 0.76
percent at 6505.16, with gains among media stocks countering falls
in financial shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
