<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Rise Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks rose broadly
Monday in hope that the monetary tightening cycle, which started
last June, is nearing an end.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 108.54 or 1.04
percent at 10,557.84 and the technology heavy Nasdaq composite
index rose 129.27 or 3.35 percent at 3,989.83.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mostly higher. The Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index rose 21.54 at 1,486.00.
</P>
<P>
The market rallied as investors sought technology and financial
stocks in hope that the Federal Reserve will remain on hold at the
monetary policy meeting on June 27-28.
</P>
<P>
Merrill Lynch, the Global Securities Research &AMP; Economics Group,
said in its latest weekly report that with inflation remaining
tame, it's almost certain that the Federal reserve won't act at
the forthcoming meeting. "Beyond that, we are increasingly
convinced that the current Federal tightening cycle is at an end,"
the report said.
</P>
<P>
Intel rose sharply after the company announced that it will
invest 2 billion U.S. dollars in a new plan in Ireland. Hewlett-
Packard and Rambus were also higher.
</P>
<P>
The financial stocks rebounded from a fall on Friday. Investors
sold stocks on that day in fears that higher rates would take a
toll on profit earnings.
</P>
<P>
Optimism over interest rates helped the market overcome an
earnings warning from Honeywell International. The company said it
will miss expectations of earnings in the second quarter.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 4.67 at 654.35 and the Russell 2000 index
of smaller companies rose 9.06 at 522.79. But the American Stock
Exchange index fell 1.63 at 934.27.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 5-to-4 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,518 up, 1,379 down and 500
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 916.14 million shares from 1.21 billion
in the previous session. 
</P>
